### Code blocks

There are only fenced code blocks starting and ending with a line of of backticks.

```
// example code block
fmt.Printf("%q", "hi!!")
```


### Blockquote

Blockquotes start with an `>` on the paragraph or on each line, and are closed with two newlines. They can be nested with multiple `>` prefixed

> Example blockquote with a single `>`
spanning multiple lines

> first quote
>> second quote
>>> third quote
> **first** quote again


### Horizontal Rulers

Rulers are three or more `-` characters in a line without any spaces.

---


## Inline Markup

### Code

Inline `code` is enclosed in single backticks.

### Italic

An __italic__ sequence of words are enclosed with `__`.

### Bold

A **bold** sequence of words are enclosed with `**`.

### Strikethrough

A ~~strikethrough~~ sequence of words are enclosed with `~~`.

